title: Wall Street Breakfast July 29: China Competition Bill, CHIPS Act Goes to Biden to Sign
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: Biden met with Xi as Congress passed China competition bill. WH says U.S. economy is in state of transition, not recession. Elon Musk says inflation may be easing, Bill Ackman scoffs at Fed at neutral. Catch today’s WSB article here.
